de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.testCases
Class SolutionProcessor

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.testCases.SolutionProcessor

public class SolutionProcessor
extends java.lang.Object

The SolutionProcessor stores information about the solutions found during the symbolic execution of a program. It provides access to these information. Furthermore, if offers the method generateTestCases() which can be uses to process the solutions found in order to generate test cases from them. If this operation is successful, the test cases are written to a file that be run with JUnit.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-08-29
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

getTestCaseEliminationFigures

public long[] getTestCaseEliminationFigures()
Return information about the elimination of test cases. The returned long array has three dimensions:
  • The first one is the number of solutions supplied to the solution processor.
  • The second one is the number of solutions that are not redundant but that have not undergone the elimination process.
  • The third one is the number of solutions that are actually used for test cases.
If any number is -1 it has not been calculated, yet.

Returns:
Information about the elimination of test cases.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - If test case generation has not been started, yet.
See Also:
hasFinishedDeletingRedudancy(), hasFinishedElimination()

getDeletingRedudancySolutionCurrentlyProcessed

public long getDeletingRedudancySolutionCurrentlyProcessed()
Get the number of the solution currently processed while deleting redundancy from the solutions. The value only has any meaning while the test case generation has been started and deleting redundancy is not finished, yet. In any other case, -1 will be returned.

Returns:
The number of the solution currently processed while deleting redundancy, or -1 if not currently deleting redundancy.

Parameters:
deletingRedudancySolutionCurrentlyProcessed - The number of the solution currently processed.

getEliminationSolutionsDropped

public long getEliminationSolutionsDropped()
Get the number of solutions already dropped while eliminating test cases based on the solutions' contribution to the coverages. The value only has any meaning while the test case generation has been started and test case elimination is not finished, yet. In any other case, -1 will be returned.

Returns:
The number of solutions already dropped while eliminating test cases, or -1 if not currently eliminating test cases.

increaseEliminationSolutionsKept

interrupt

public void interrupt()
Interrupt processing of test cases. This method must not be called unless the actual processing has been started. Processing will not stop immediately but at the nearest point where the test case generation algorithm or any of its utilized algorithms check whether they should continue, or not.

Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - If test case generation has not been started, yet.

isInterrupted

boolean isInterrupted()
Check if the test case generation has been interrupted. This method has package visibility as it is only meant to be used by utilized test case generation algorithms.

Returns:
true, if test case generation has been interupted; false if it has not or has not yet started.
